  "prompt": "Whom was Muhammad worshipping before getting revelations?",
  "response": "Before receiving revelations, Muhammad, like many people in Mecca, was part of a society that practiced polytheism. The pre-Islamic Arabs worshipped a variety of deities, with Allah being recognized as a high god but not worshipped exclusively. There is limited direct information about Muhammad\u2019s personal religious practices before his first revelation at the age of 40. However, it is commonly believed that he was part of the Hanif tradition, a group of monotheists who maintained a belief in one God but did not follow Judaism or Christianity. The concept of being a \"Hanif\" suggests that he was inclined towards monotheism and sought the religion of Abraham.",
